The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the asymmetric traveling salesman problem on graphs with bounded orientable or non-orientable genus. This involves techniques from graph theory, combinatorial optimization, and computational geometry, which are typically covered in the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on designing efficient algorithms for solving a geometric optimization problem on graphs with a specific topological structure. The other categories are also relevant, as they provide theoretical foundations and insights into the complexity and approximability of the problem.
